I. RDP (remote desktop protocol) 
    -gives user a gui to connect via network connection
    -FreeRDP (free imp of RDP)
    -works in a client/server model (remote/users must have rdp software installed

ii. VNC (virtual network computing) 
    -server-client protocol --permits user accounts to remotely connect & control distance system
        by gui
iii. Zoho Assist
    -remote software permits access & support Linux desktops servers w/o remote cxn protocols like: RDP
    VNC, or SSH
    -2factor auth

Apps: software for accessing remotely
Client/Server App:
1. TigerVNC
      -permits users to launch & interact w/graphical apps on remote machines
      -implement TLS encryption
2. RealVNC (devel screen sharing tech w/products: VNC Connect & VNC Viewer
    features: admin unattended sys't 
              -get VNC to connect for free for home use
              -subscription req for pro & ent
3. TeamViewer
    -good for personal; premium for business users
    -file transfer, remote deskop sharing
4. REmmina (written in GTK+3)
    -for sysadmin & travelers
    -supports multiple network protocols: RDP, VNC, NX XDMCP & SSH
5. NoMachine
    -offers a secure personal server
6. Apache Guacamole
    -supports std protocols: VNC, RDP, SSH
    -employs HTML5 web ie web browsers
7. XRDP (based on FreeRDP & desktop)
    -integrates w/LikwiseOpen 
    -log into Ubuntu server via RDP w/active dir username/pw
    -needs redacting
8. FreeNX
    -a secure (SSH-based) client/server sys't
    -core lib provided by NoMachine
    -Distro: deb: wiki.debian.org/freenx
             CentOS: wiki.centos.org/HowTos/FreeNX
             Ubutu: help.ubuntu.com/community/FreeNX
             
